23-OCT-1994 J\"org Knappen (knappen@vkpmzd.kph.uni-mainz.de)

        * [.vms]make_sauter_pk.com: Rounded the true sizes to two trailing
          digits for the canonical magsteps. This is in accordance to the
          practice of DEK (plain TeX) and of the LaTeX3 team.

          Changed the logic of the command procedure as suggested by
          Christian Spieler <SPIELER@linac.ikp.physik.th-darmstadt.de>:
          Write the small mf file first and call it afterwards. This has
          the advantage, that the jobname equals the final fontname and
          is recorded properly by the special definitions of modes.mf
          maintained by Karl Berry.

          Note, that these modifications aren't yet applied to the UNIX and
          DOS batch files.
      
 4-SEP-1994 J\"org Knappen (knappen@vkpmzd.kph.uni-mainz.de)

        * [.vms]make_sauter_pk.com: Added magstep sizes for
          nominal sizes 30 and 36.

 3-SEP-1994 J\"org Knappen (knappen@vkpmzd.kph.uni-mainz.de)

        * Renamed b-circle.mf to b-lcircle.mf and
          b-circlew.mf to b-lcirclew.mf in accordance to 
          current LaTeX policy. Suggested by Tomas Valter Vanhala 
          <vanhala@cc.helsinki.fi>

          Also changed them to include c-lcircle, and changed the
          name of c-circle.mf to c-lcircle.mf for consistency.

 3-SEP-1994 J\"org Knappen (knappen@vkpmzd.kph.uni-mainz.de)

        * Added two new files:
          b-cmbxsc for bold extended small caps
          b-cmrs   for roman Sperrsatz fonts (letterspaced)

 3-SEP-1994 J\"org Knappen (knappen@vkpmzd.kph.uni-mainz.de)

        * Reorganised the directory structure: Split the mf files into
          subdirectories:
          - base contains those Sauter files, which faithfully reproduce
            the standard cm fonts
          - addons contains additional fonts like LaTeX symbols, Cyrillic,
            Wasy symbols, Jeffrey fonts, other cm variations like
            cmbxsc (Computer Modern Bold eXtended Small Caps)

 3-SEP-1994 J\"org Knappen (knappen@vkpmzd.kph.uni-mainz.de)
        
        * b-cmcsc.mf: Completely reworked. Removed discontinouities
          introduced in version 2.0. Restored John Sauter's original
          formulae above 10pt and adjusted *all* parameters to the AMS
          extracm fonts cmcsc9 and cmcsc8.

